#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""ms-coverage — Mediastack Topology & Coverage Scanner

Scans the ENTIRE codebase and produces a structured coverage map:
  - Every API route (method + path + handler + file)
  - Every DB table and its columns
  - Every infra provider and its deploy/remove methods
  - Every app manifest (catalog)
  - Every frontend view and its API calls
  - Every wizard step function
  - Which of the above has test coverage (and what kind)

Output: data/coverage_map.json  (consumed by the topology dashboard)
        data/coverage_report.txt (human-readable summary)

Usage:
  ms-coverage             # scan + report
  ms-coverage --json      # JSON only (for dashboard consumption)
  ms-coverage --gaps      # show only uncovered items
  ms-coverage --section X # filter by section (routes/tables/providers/manifests/views/steps)

Install: sudo ln -sf /srv/mediastack/ms-coverage /usr/local/bin/ms-coverage
"""
